snippet: God’s Love We Deliver, a provider of meals to sick people, sold its air rights for a condominium development to finance an expansion of its building. But some residents object to the plan.
abstract: Gods Love We Deliver charity, provider of meals to sick people, angers residents of New York City's SoHo neighborhood by selling air rights for condominium development to finance expansion of its building; group plans to sell $4 million of its rights to a developer planning a 14-story condo and will begin its own $26 million renovation of its 60-year-old two-story building.
lead_paragraph: God’s Love We Deliver, a provider of meals to sick people, sold its air rights for a condominium development to finance an expansion of its building. But some residents object to the plan.

headline.seo: SoHo’s God’s Love We Deliver Faces Obstacle to Expansion
headline.main: SoHo Nonprofit’s Expansion Upsets Some Neighbors
